International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Thu 27 Jun 2013
Source: TVNZ (New Zealand), ONE News report [edited]
http://tvnz.co.nz/world-news/italian-family-paralysed-poisonous-herb-mix-up-5478723


An Italian grandmother and her family have been left paralysed after she accidentally garnished their dinner with a poisonous herb.

[The 66-year-old woman], her husband, daughter, and young grandson were found vomiting, or collapsed and paralysed on the floor, by another family member.

They were rushed to hospital, where they have been put into a medically-induced coma, AFP [Agence France-Presse] reported Italian media as saying.

It is understood that the woman found the poisonous plant, devil's trumpet, in some bushes near a market, and believing it to be a type of bitter green broccoli, took some home and planted it in her herb garden.

She sprinkled it over the family's pasta dinner on Monday [24 Jun 2013]. Shortly afterwards they all began to feel ill.

"I can't forget the image of my mother and sister paralysed on the floor," [the woman's son], is quoted as saying. "I saw my family members falling ill one by one. After my nephew starting being sick, I realised that all of their symptoms were related to something that they had eaten."

Devil's trumpet, or _Datura metel_, is highly toxic and can be fatal if ingested by humans or animals.

The 4 are still in hospital but doctors said they are confident the paralysis would be temporary.

